	<div class="div4">BAPUNAGAR </div>
<h3> 1. Location & Connectivity 🧭</h3>
<ul>
<li>Eastern Ahmedabad sector, postcode 382330, in AMC wards 21, 28, 29 

<li>Situated near Narol–Naroda Road (NH‑8A) and close to the Sardar Patel Ring Road, offering strong regional access 

<li>Well served by public transport:

<li>AMC/ BRTS buses: frequent services; bus stops like Bapunagar Char Rasta, L.B. Shastri Stadium (~ 1–3 min walk) 

<li>Ahmedabad Metro Line 1: nearest station ~19 min walk (Apparel Park / Kankaria East) 

<li>Nearby railway stations (Asarwa, Ahmedabad Junction ~4–6 km) and Sardar Vallabhbhai Patel International Airport (~11 km) 
</ul>
<h3> 2. History & Demographics 🏘️</h3>
<ul>
<li>Developed in the 1960s as mill-workers’ housing; textile mills ceased by late 1980s 

<li>Transitioned to home-based industries, including diamond cutting—now India’s #2 hub after Surat—and cottage manufacturing (e.g., detergent precursor to Nirma) 

<li>Nicknamed “Mini‑Saurashtra” due to large influx from Saurashtra, plus migrants from UP, Rajasthan, Maharashtra 
</ul>
<h3> 3. Built Environment & Economy 🌆</h3>
<ul>
<li>68% residential, dense mix of row-houses and walk-up flats 


<li>Commercial: local shops, weekly markets, informal businesses

<li>Industrial/commercial precincts: diamond cutting centers, small factories 

</ul>
<h3>4. Infrastructure & Amenities 🏫 </h3>
<ul>
<li>Education: Vidhyanagar High School, Axay High School, Shri Jivan Sadhana HSSC, several municipal/state schools + nearby colleges 


<li>Healthcare: ESIC Hospital, Kakadia Hospital, Matru Hospital, Star/Samjuba Hospitals, many clinics

<li>Commercial & Community: D‑Mart, local markets, parks (though limited), Lal Bahadur Shastri Stadium (now Sardar Patel Stadium) and historic Malik Saban Roza 
</ul>

<h3>5. Urban Challenges & Developments 🚧  </h3>
<ul>
<li>Encroachment clearance: AMC razed 450 houses by Malek Saban lake recently 


<li>Infrastructure issues: sinkholes near Nehrunagar Circle & Raghunath HS; AMC working on repairs 


<li>Food safety raids: sauce factory in Bapunagar had ~4,200 kg of inedible sauce destroyed 



<li>Safety concerns: serious crime reported—case of sexual assault on a minor reported in the area 
</ul>
<h3>✅ Summary</h3>
<ul>
<h3>Pros:</h3>

<li>Excellent connectivity (roads, buses, metro, airport).

<li>Strong community infrastructure—schools, hospitals, markets, stadium.

<li>Affordable yet appreciating real estate market.

<li>Vibrant small-scale economy: diamond cutting, retail, services.

<h3>Cons:</h3>

<li>High density with limited green spaces.

<li>Infrastructure challenges: occasional sinkages, encroachment-free drive impact.

<li>Some concerns around public health and safety.
</ul>
</ol>
